wiki_structure.title: EIGEN High-Fidelity Information Extraction from Document Images Wiki
wiki_structure.description: Documentation for the EIGEN project, a joint learning aggregation approach for high-fidelity information extraction from document images.

page.title: Introduction to EIGEN
page.description: EIGEN is a project for high-fidelity information extraction from document images, utilizing a joint learning aggregation approach.

page.title: Training and Labeling Functions
page.description: This page describes the training and labeling functions used in the EIGEN project, including the main.py file and its associated functions.

page.title: Model Training and Integration
page.description: This page provides an overview of the model training and integration process in the EIGEN project, including the Cage_cords.ipynb and NH_cage.ipynb files.

page.title: Demo Notebooks and Inference
page.description: This page provides examples of demo notebooks used in the EIGEN project, including the cords_demo.ipynb and nh_demo.ipynb files, and describes the inference process.
